Bring a large #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the noodles. Trim and halve the @green beans{150}. Trim the @carrot{1} (no need to peel). Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the carrot. Stop when you get to the carrot centre. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, and keep to one side for later.

> Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, pour the @Szechuan paste{100%g} into a #medium bowl{}. Add the @water for the sauce{100%ml}, the lime zest and a squeeze of lime juice. Mix well to combine and keep aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @beef strips{240%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Fry until browned, ~{1-2%minutes}, continuously stirring.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw beef.

> Don't crowd the pan or your beef strips will stew not fry! It's best to cook it in batches.

Once each batch of beef is browned, remove it to rest on a #kitchen paper lined plate{}. The beef is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Wipe out the now empty frying pan and heat a drizzle of oil on high heat. Add the carrot, green beans and garlic and stir-fry until the veg is tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Continue to stir while it cooks.

Once the vegetables are cooked, pour in your sauce, allow it to bubble for a minute then add the cooked noodles and beef strips. Toss well to coat everything in the sauce. Allow it to cook until everything is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes} (keep stirring). Take the pan off the heat, taste and season with a little salt or more lime juice if you feel it needs it.

> Add a splash more water if it has become a little dry.

Divide the Szechuan beef noodles between your #bowls{}, scatter over the spring onion and tuck in. Enjoy!